<subSubSection id="78B7C7255D59257FE95877F5237C4D23" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="96ADE0A4B9175E521EDDCAF6DC8C2AAE" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A7B590B4C6A5E2BD12E44F1D729C29A1" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="C245AAF50CDC132CEC57A87611EC4F06" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="89A9A618AD2F747FE021C2BE9D729B27" captionStart="Figure 24" captionStartId="F24" captionText="Figure 24. Distribution of S. forsskalii." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.198.79514.figure24" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689717" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">24</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4DE462C08A58E247D1F90099799F6E49" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum forskalii" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="forskalii">
<emphasis id="C5E83BD6123082A41CE07E5593E2FAD8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum forskalii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found from northeastern Africa and Arabian Peninsula to Pakistan and western India (Rajasthan and Gujarat).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6BC073B384A2BB5EB659A49FC24ED491" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="F0CD5DE76246644589DB9272076842E4" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ecology and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="44ABDB05BB66D92E787FFD682F5AE542" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="6625946267F3E0EBC91073EF7580045A" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum forskalii" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="forskalii">
<emphasis id="0917EE58BA29BF77115D7F6AC06C1E87" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum forskalii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a desert plant growing on stony ground and rocky slopes, often on granite, elevation not recorded on herbarium sheets we have seen from India (from sea level to 2,000 m elevation fide 
<bibRefCitation id="CCEE32AE989760DA0AA350FB6F092313" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF03027161" author="Vorontsova, MS" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany Monographs" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 428" refId="B259" refString="Vorontsova, MS, Knapp, S, 2016. A revision of the &quot;spiny solanums,&quot; Solanum subgenus Leptostemonum (Solanaceae), in Africa and Madagascar. Systematic Botany Monographs 99: 1 - 428, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/BF03027161" title="A revision of the &quot; spiny solanums, &quot; Solanum subgenus Leptostemonum (Solanaceae), in Africa and Madagascar." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF03027161" volume="99" year="2016">Vorontsova and Knapp 2016</bibRefCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4033362950EA1202666078D236123A6C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="common names and uses">
<paragraph id="BF7D2283CA50573A432A0F0D5DEA3479" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Common names and uses.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7B8B1F6FC435F9D7EC7D9801BC4C80DC" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
India. Rajasthan: nar-kanta [Hindi] (
<bibRefCitation id="448B898C08C11C8619D3A32F3BDE88D5" author="Singh, V" editor="Shetty, BV" journalOrPublisher="2. Botanical Survey of India, Calcutta" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="562 - 579" refId="B227" refString="Singh, V, 1991. Solanaceae. In: Shetty, BV, Singh, V, Eds., Flora of Rajasthan Vol. 2. Botanical Survey of India, Calcutta: 562 - 579" title="Solanaceae." volumeTitle="Flora of Rajasthan Vol." year="1991">Singh 1991</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName id="86A12179CB92AC4CE59A81133F8BC945" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. albicaule" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="albicaule">
<emphasis id="78AE1B65BD9CEFE6C754E1572A370918" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. albicaule</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8D78AF768E7223AF55BFB926D5633C2B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="conservation status">
<paragraph id="9DAF09EDF6EF3A0DB293A9A3329727E9" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Conservation status</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B767DFE37B06A716E3F4F4F9A155D288" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="CFDB0627D3C456BC2895BBD1C34D10A2" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
(
<bibRefCitation id="4C0CE6B3CC34AC864A57968AF4F48950" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2305/IUCN.UK.2021-1.RLTS.T101526207A101526210.en" author="Knapp, S" journalOrPublisher="Anales del Jardin Botanico de Madrid" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B126" refString="Knapp, S, 2021b. Solanum forskalii. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2021: e.T101526207A101526210. https://doi.org/10.2305/IUCN.UK.2021-1.RLTS.T101526207A101526210.en" title="Solanum forskalii. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2021: e. T 101526207 A 101526210." url="https://doi.org/10.2305/IUCN.UK.2021-1.RLTS.T101526207A101526210.en" year="2021 b">Knapp 2021b</bibRefCitation>
).
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="082C7C20EFA347C7B4D59ADB090F9FEC" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum forskalii" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="forskalii">
<emphasis id="15238481AB313224041E16ADBBB852B4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum forskalii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been formally assessed as least concern (LC; https://www.iucnredlist.org/species/101526207/101526210).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F9B4762382550BC60950E307B5209274" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="DC90D9F3D74337FCF5E7F8F0AE683BBA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="071408CB885A0BD17AFE3BC7C2CA9B48" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Although 
<bibRefCitation id="5064A3913AC3BCEC1AF995FB9F576B11" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF03027161" author="Vorontsova, MS" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany Monographs" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 428" refId="B259" refString="Vorontsova, MS, Knapp, S, 2016. A revision of the &quot;spiny solanums,&quot; Solanum subgenus Leptostemonum (Solanaceae), in Africa and Madagascar. Systematic Botany Monographs 99: 1 - 428, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/BF03027161" title="A revision of the &quot; spiny solanums, &quot; Solanum subgenus Leptostemonum (Solanaceae), in Africa and Madagascar." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF03027161" volume="99" year="2016">Vorontsova and Knapp (2016)</bibRefCitation>
suggested collections of 
<taxonomicName id="84F42F71AA5B8E80219A55E442434303" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. forskalii" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="forskalii">
<emphasis id="C40BAE4368D7EA3337A3D5BF50738319" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. forskalii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from India might be accidental introductions, it is reported as fairly common in the Indian state of Rajasthan (
<bibRefCitation id="2D81960121FB6C427153926D55AF1956" author="Singh, V" editor="Shetty, BV" journalOrPublisher="2. Botanical Survey of India, Calcutta" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="562 - 579" refId="B227" refString="Singh, V, 1991. Solanaceae. In: Shetty, BV, Singh, V, Eds., Flora of Rajasthan Vol. 2. Botanical Survey of India, Calcutta: 562 - 579" title="Solanaceae." volumeTitle="Flora of Rajasthan Vol." year="1991">Singh 1991</bibRefCitation>
). It is easily recognised by its white-coloured stems, resulting from the dense pubescence of overlapping stellate trichomes with long, delicate rays, and abundant, recurved prickles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="12613F56D54410F517FCB2AED021FAEA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="16B7C4F9CF90E8A74B88E6D97EF3B67E" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum forskalii" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="forskalii">
<emphasis id="65B6F2820F405C63E7F24477FC30312A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum forskalii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="09EC3131439E26CD6BE4948684B42CF4" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. cordatum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="cordatum">
<emphasis id="5FA96A39FECE234629F7E6903A087A12" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. cordatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its porrect trichomes with 6-10 rays over 0.15 mm long on the young stems (versus trichomes with 12-18 rays under 0.15 mm long on the young stems of 
<taxonomicName id="9024F1DAE161D0F52B06A746BA90920A" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. cordatum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="cordatum">
<emphasis id="1DF6C706560BDC35AB1DB0776467B1F7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. cordatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), 1-20 flowers per inflorescence (versus 1-2 flowers per inflorescence in 
<taxonomicName id="15670C89B95BC40398B481F419EC7F2F" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. cordatum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="cordatum">
<emphasis id="98C28114C66EDF8F4C711E9D48B17686" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. cordatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and anthers 4.5-7 mm long (versus anthers 3-5 mm long in 
<taxonomicName id="8D29B35708BCE90078645EA2CF687EBD" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. cordatum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="cordatum">
<emphasis id="F00252FC1867C27170365DCE40A1C8E8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. cordatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The trichome rays of 
<taxonomicName id="AFBF0DD7347014599C5C74A99C8B5D5E" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. forskalii" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="forskalii">
<emphasis id="9BBBDE7F3723D7B2B3BC4902F0B65CE3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. forskalii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are much thinner and more delicate than those of 
<taxonomicName id="7CDE63071126AE22D5C68FC05669D46F" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. cordatum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="cordatum">
<emphasis id="41399233E95859E99E3DB832839B20FF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. cordatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which appear stout and almost lepidote. There is considerable variability within 
<taxonomicName id="83132442F85BA359F9CF980C01500D5C" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. forskalii" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="forskalii">
<emphasis id="AD485039B712BE6BC4B4A026E2937FA7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. forskalii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Africa with respect to inflorescence length, prickle size and trichome midpoint length (
<bibRefCitation id="737155EB7C79B152E2BB834B6ADFD94A" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF03027161" author="Vorontsova, MS" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany Monographs" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 428" refId="B259" refString="Vorontsova, MS, Knapp, S, 2016. A revision of the &quot;spiny solanums,&quot; Solanum subgenus Leptostemonum (Solanaceae), in Africa and Madagascar. Systematic Botany Monographs 99: 1 - 428, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/BF03027161" title="A revision of the &quot; spiny solanums, &quot; Solanum subgenus Leptostemonum (Solanaceae), in Africa and Madagascar." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF03027161" volume="99" year="2016">Vorontsova and Knapp 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="1C788A80029078A013346BE51F498B9C" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.198.79514.figure24" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689717" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 24" startId="F24">
<paragraph id="6C3C59342A6320247BC08B2F09727E0A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="6CEC5753F97FA732C64AFBCF417DA0E8" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Figure 24.</emphasis>
Distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="4F02ECC9FD76931A1C146660188E9E34" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. forsskalii" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="forsskalii">
<emphasis id="B231E48F299B3A7B685FB381A02DB77E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. forsskalii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
